  introContent={`
    <p>Islamabad Electric Supply Company (IESCO) supplies electricity to over 3.2 million consumers across five districts: <strong>Islamabad Capital Territory (ICT)</strong>, <strong>Rawalpindi</strong>, <strong>Attock</strong>, <strong>Jhelum</strong>, and <strong>Chakwal</strong>. Established in 1998, IESCO is unique among Pakistan's DISCOs because it serves the nation's federal capital — supplying electricity to government ministries, diplomatic missions, the Supreme Court, parliament, and all of Islamabad's modern sectors alongside millions of residential consumers.</p>
    <p>IESCO's Islamabad coverage includes all city sectors (F-sectors, G-sectors, I-sectors, E-sectors), Blue Area (the commercial hub), and major housing societies like DHA Islamabad, Bahria Town, and CBR Town. In Rawalpindi, IESCO supplies the entire district including Rawalpindi Cantt, Taxila (home to Pakistan's heaviest industry and Heavy Industries Taxila), Wah Cantt, and the scenic Murree hills. The company also covers Attock, Jhelum, and Chakwal districts with their significant cement, oil, and industrial facilities.</p>
    <p>To check your IESCO bill online, enter your <strong>14-digit IESCO reference number</strong> in the bill checker above. Both Islamabad and Rawalpindi consumers use the same 14-digit reference number format. Your reference number is printed at the top of every IESCO bill. The IESCO helpline numbers differ by city: <strong>051-9252626</strong> for Islamabad and <strong>051-9272626</strong> for Rawalpindi.</p>
    <p>IESCO serves a high proportion of government and professional consumers. Many Islamabad consumers have their bills deducted automatically from salaries or allowances — but checking your bill every month is still important to detect errors, verify units, and track your energy usage against Protected/Unprotected status.</p>
    <p>PakistanBill.online is <strong>Pakistan's only platform</strong> covering all 19 utility providers. Alongside this checker, you can also check: <a href="/lesco-bill/">LESCO bill</a> | <a href="/pesco-bill/">PESCO bill</a> | <a href="/gepco-bill/">GEPCO bill</a> | <a href="/sngpl-bill/">SNGPL gas bill</a> | <a href="/wasa-rawalpindi-bill/">WASA Rawalpindi</a>. Use our free <a href="/electricity-bill-calculator/">electricity bill calculator</a> to estimate charges before your bill arrives, or visit our <a href="/dashboard/">universal bill dashboard</a> to check multiple bills without switching pages. Also see: <a href="/blog/iesco-reference-number/">How to find your IESCO reference number</a> — and our complete <a href="/islamabad/">Islamabad & Rawalpindi utility bills guide</a>.</p>
  `}

  howToSteps={[
    "Find your 14-digit IESCO reference number — printed in bold at the top of your IESCO electricity bill. Both Islamabad and Rawalpindi consumers have a 14-digit reference number.",
    "Open the bill checker at the top of this page. The Reference Number tab is selected by default.",
    "Enter your 14-digit IESCO reference number in the input field. Numbers only — no spaces or dashes.",
    "Click Check Bill. The tool connects to bill.pitc.com.pk/iescobill and fetches your current bill.",
    "Your complete IESCO bill appears in 3 to 5 seconds — showing total amount due, due date, units consumed, meter readings, and all charges.",
    "Click Download PDF to save as a PDF file, or click Print to immediately print your IESCO duplicate bill."
  ]}

  billReadingTips={[
    "Your IESCO reference number is the same whether you live in Islamabad F-sector, Rawalpindi Saddar, Taxila, or Murree. All IESCO connections have a 14-digit reference number in the same format.",
    "Government employees whose IESCO bills are paid through salary deduction should still check their bill monthly. Errors in unit readings or Protected/Unprotected classification can result in overpayment even when auto-deducted.",
    "Islamabad DHA and Bahria Town residents often have high consumption due to large homes and multiple ACs. Track your 6-month average carefully — crossing 200 units average triggers Unprotected status which roughly doubles your per-unit cost.",
    "Rawalpindi Cantt consumers: bills for cantonment areas are managed by IESCO. If you previously had a separate cantonment authority bill and now have IESCO, your reference number changed — check with the IESCO Rawalpindi office at 051-9272626.",
    "The FPA charge on your IESCO bill is set by NEPRA monthly and is the same percentage for all DISCOs nationwide. A high FPA in winter months (when expensive thermal plants run) can add Rs 100–400 to typical household bills.",
    "Murree and hill station consumers: power supply to high-altitude areas is managed by IESCO's Murree sub-division. Winter consumption for heating can push mountain-area consumers into Unprotected status — monitor consumption carefully.",
  ]}

  savingTips={[
    "Islamabad and Rawalpindi consumers: Islamabad's relatively mild climate means AC is less critical than Lahore or Karachi. Use ceiling fans and natural ventilation for the maximum number of months to maintain Protected status.",
    "Government offices in Islamabad typically have inefficient lighting and AC systems. Replacing old fluorescent lights with LED and upgrading to inverter ACs cuts government building electricity costs by 30–50%.",
    "Bahria Town and DHA Islamabad residents: large homes with multiple ACs should use smart AC controllers to schedule cooling. Running ACs only when rooms are occupied and setting strict temperature limits saves 200–400 units monthly.",
    "Apply for IESCO net metering if you install rooftop solar. Islamabad receives excellent solar irradiance, and the capital's high-income residential areas have some of the highest solar adoption rates in Pakistan. Net metering eliminates most monthly bills.",
    "Taxila and Wah Cantt industrial consumers: shift production lines that allow flexible timing to off-peak hours. Industrial units with large motors and compressors benefit most from off-peak operation.",
    "Use IESCO's online complaint system. Filing billing complaints online at iesco.com.pk creates a digital record that is harder for IESCO to ignore than phone complaints.",
  ]}

  complaintProcess={[
    "Call IESCO Islamabad at 051-9252626 or IESCO Rawalpindi at 051-9272626 with your 14-digit reference number ready. State the complaint clearly and get a Complaint Registration Number (CRN).",
    "For Islamabad sector offices, visit the nearest IESCO sub-division office with your bill and CNIC. F-sector and G-sector offices are the most accessible for Islamabad residents.",
    "IESCO must resolve billing complaints within 14 working days under NEPRA regulations. Track your complaint using the CRN.",
    "Escalate to NEPRA at 0800-63000 (toll-free) if IESCO does not respond within 14 working days. File online at nepra.org.pk with your CRN.",
    "For diplomatic mission or government building billing disputes, IESCO has a dedicated commercial and government accounts division — contact the IESCO head office at Golra Morr, Islamabad directly.",
  ]}

