  faqs={[
    { question: "How do I check my IESCO bill online in March 2026?", answer: "Enter your 14-digit IESCO reference number in the bill checker above and click Check Bill. Your complete IESCO electricity bill appears in seconds — covering Islamabad or Rawalpindi — with amount due, due date, units consumed, and all charges. Free, no login, 24/7." },
    { question: "Is the IESCO bill checker the same for Islamabad and Rawalpindi?", answer: "Yes. All IESCO consumers — whether in Islamabad F-7, Rawalpindi Saddar, Taxila, Wah Cantt, Murree, Attock, Jhelum, or Chakwal — use the same 14-digit reference number format. Enter your reference number in the checker above and it works regardless of your city within IESCO's coverage area." },
    { question: "What is the IESCO helpline for Islamabad vs Rawalpindi?", answer: "IESCO Islamabad helpline is 051-9252626. IESCO Rawalpindi helpline is 051-9272626. For 24/7 outage emergencies, call the national WAPDA helpline 118. For billing disputes, use the city-specific numbers above during business hours (9 AM to 5 PM, Monday to Friday)." },
    { question: "How do I download my IESCO duplicate bill?", answer: "After your bill loads in the checker above, click Download PDF. Select Save as PDF in the browser print dialog and click Save. Your IESCO duplicate bill saves instantly as a PDF — ready to email, share on WhatsApp, or present at a bank or JazzCash outlet for payment." },
    { question: "How do I pay my IESCO bill online?", answer: "Pay through JazzCash, Easypaisa, HBL, MCB, Meezan, or any bank mobile app. Go to Bill Payments, select Electricity, choose IESCO, enter your 14-digit reference number, verify the amount, and confirm. Payment reflects in IESCO's system within 2 to 4 hours." },
    { question: "How do government employees in Islamabad check their IESCO bill?", answer: "Government employees whose IESCO bills are deducted from salary should still check their bill monthly using the tool above with their 14-digit reference number. This verifies the correct amount is being deducted and confirms your Protected or Unprotected status. Errors in salary-deducted bills do occur and must be caught by the consumer." },
    { question: "Which areas of Islamabad does IESCO cover?", answer: "IESCO covers all of Islamabad Capital Territory including all city sectors (F-1 through F-17, G-sectors, I-sectors, E-sectors), Blue Area, industrial areas, and all major housing societies including DHA Islamabad, Bahria Town, and CBR Town. IESCO also supplies electricity to the ICT's rural union councils and villages." },
    { question: "Does IESCO cover Rawalpindi Cantonment?", answer: "Rawalpindi Cantt areas within IESCO's territory are supplied by IESCO. However, some parts of Rawalpindi Cantt may be managed separately by the Cantonment Board for water and sanitation — but electricity is IESCO. Check your bill heading to confirm your supplier. If it says IESCO, use this tool with your 14-digit reference number." },
    { question: "What is the grace period for IESCO bill payment?", answer: "IESCO gives 7 days after the due date to pay without a late payment surcharge. After the grace period, a 10% surcharge applies to the unpaid amount. Islamabad consumers with salary-deducted bills should ensure their employer processes the deduction on time to avoid this surcharge." },
    { question: "How do I check the IESCO load shedding schedule for my area?", answer: "Visit ccms.pitc.com.pk and enter your 14-digit IESCO reference number. Your specific feeder's load shedding schedule appears. Islamabad city areas typically experience 2–4 hours of load shedding; Rawalpindi outer areas and Attock, Jhelum, Chakwal may experience more. IESCO prioritizes uninterrupted supply to diplomatic zones and government buildings." },
  ]}

